Us last night ??. What a gorgeous evening socialising with the finest creatives who are supporting the growth of the Northern Powerhouse! And it was indeed a growth project that claimed our category last night. 27 derelict guest houses in Morecambe which now proudly form 44 family homes. With my ?Northern Hat on Im happy to see the derelict homes now filled with new love and the scale of what they have achieved is something to be very proud of indeed. Obviously though we were both a little disappointed as we are all about achieving our goals and being the best. I always see bumps in the road where we dont achieve our desired objective as character building and a little reminder that this is a journey of twists and turns. Its these twists and turns (and a few bumps) that build our souls, and makes us into genuine beautiful people ??????

Date nights?

Andy and I love a good date night. Far and few between now though. We order what we actually want. No toys at the table. Uninterrupted adult conversation. Wine. Eat as soon as were served. No toilet breaks. A little bit of peace and quiet. Then we start talking about him more and more. Wonder what hes doing. Ring him to find out what hes doing. Send pics please. We miss him. 
So we moved on to bigger better things. Usually at our lovely local. Same table, extra chair. Or a special night in. We plan them and he gets excited. We still have wine. None for Brooks. Our dinner simplifies and we have His conversations while toys fly across the table. He loves it. We love it. Family date nights for the win. Who has them?

data.text:
DANIEL so excited as the flowergirls, bridesmaids and then GABBY appeared over the crest of the hill.  Theirs was a wedding embracing Daniel's Jewish background and Gabby's Catholic faith, and a combined spirituality that is actually quite similar!  Here you can see Daniel's attendants, supporting the chuppah, and his parents to his right.  The chuppah evokes the marital home and, when Gabby joined Daniel beneath it, they circled each other, creating an exclusive space around their symbolic new home, marking their transition into married life together.  It was also a very welcomed canopy of shade, being a 38 degrees celcius day at @maviseskitchen that day!  More details about this incredibly beautiful day will follow. xx
